The paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing and data mining to improve the results of a qualitative study on GitHub pull requests. This involves aspects of software engineering (cs.SE) such as code merging and project management, as well as human-computer interaction (cs.HC) in terms of the subjective opinions collected from the crowd. The use of data mining also suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and potentially cybernetics (cs.CY) in terms of the predictive model built. Finally, the study's emphasis on the generalizability of the approach suggests a focus on social and information sciences (cs.SI).
